    {
      "id": "bridge-authoring-step-1",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Step 1",
      "position": {
        "x": -260,
        "y": 40
      },
      "width": 520,
      "height": 260,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Step 1: Import bridge (create)\n\nCreate a `bridge` node configured for **import**.\n\nMinimum fields:\n- `bridge.ref`: a node-class graph ref\n- `bridge.role`: `import`\n- `bridge.grants`: include `create`\n\nExpected:\n- [ ] Bridge node has a valid ref\n- [ ] Clicking it can create a node in the current graph"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "bridge-authoring-step-2",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Step 2",
      "position": {
        "x": -260,
        "y": 330
      },
      "width": 520,
      "height": 260,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Step 2: Export bridge (exposure)\n\nCreate a `bridge` node configured for **export**.\n\nExport bridges define outward exposure:\n- views (allow/deny/allowlist)\n- node classes / edge classes\n- scripts\n- declarations\n\nExpected:\n- [ ] Export bridge has an allowlist for views\n- [ ] Exposure is deterministic (same allowlist every time)"
      }
    },
